        4/18/2017
    

I've been Todd's client for seven years. He's the kind of man you're jealous of because he makes a living off his talent. What he does for a living and what he's really good at are one and the same.'Remarkably gifted' is another way to put him. I've walked into a bar and had total strangers approach me and ask, "where'd you get your hair done?" For years I've received compliments from friends old and new because of his work. He's not rushed. He's precise, meticulous. The standard haircut service is a 45 to 60 minute affair. He will go over time if it isn't flawless. He will get the fade, blend, or 'disconnect' perfect. The portfolio on his site shows how well he does polished, classic, and modern styles. Not only is that true, but he can just as easily do more 'messy' and 'edgy' looks, which I'm often after. Outside of business hours, he's continuing to refine his craft by traveling and attending various conferences to consume and learn as much as he can. And it's paid off, clearly. He now has his own place, he chooses his own product, he has his own apprentices. You really ought to try him.I enjoy my visits to his shop. He was clearly taught the art of Southern hospitality. He'll greet you with a hug, offer you a drink. In the chair he's smart, has an attractive sense of humor, he's conversational and charming. But if all you want is to relax quietly, he's just as sensitive to that as well. His store is never noisy. It's never crowded. It's never rushed.Todd also stocks quality product, including my new favorites Imperial and Layrite. For years I've preferred Kevin Murphy, but I've switched to both of these alternatives at his recommendation, and I love them.Other yelpers have already mentioned the various positives, and I agree: clean and attractive storefront, excellent taste in music selections, online scheduling is easy (Todd will schedule for you at the store if you can't). Tip: Bring cash to avoid a small card fee when paying.A final reflection: On most occasions I try my best to 'trick' Todd into giving me a bad haircut. It's never worked. I'll arrive with some wild idea about 'what I want to try next' with my hair. I'm also a terrible communicator. None of this really hinders Todd in the slightest. He listens, talks me through it, makes a couple suggestions of his own, and then works his magic. All these years I've never sat in the chair feeling 'nervous'. Only excited. And all these years I've never gotten out of the chair feeling upset, only happy.




