        10/27/2016
    

Let me start by saying this is 100% the most soul crushing haircut I've ever received. I'm a guy with a unique look, sometimes it's longer and sometimes it's shorter, but I have a certain look and feel to my hair - I've had it my whole life. It's gone now. Totally devastated. I had longer hair going in, and I asked for the same shape, but within 10 seconds I had an electric razor shearing me like I was in the Army. I'm not the same person. I'm not Adam Levine. I don't like the shaved sides. There was literally no warning. I hate how insanely short it is. So much. And I'm forced to live with it for months and months. There was no discussion, just some light banter and whooosh! instantly my persona is obliterated. It doesn't necessarily look awful - but IT ISNT WHO I AM. I'm not a "fancy hipster". I'm not what they made me into. I had a look and they killed it without second thought. I'm a musician who plays a lot of gigs, and let me tell you - I'll be be wearing a beanie for a long time. I played it off cool, because what else am I going to do when (without any warning whatsoever) someone starts shaving my head. Once you drag those f***cking shears across someones scalp, there's no going back. To my barber: don't make irreversible changes to someone who didn't ask for them. My appearance isn't something to be so reckless about. Seriously, please, for the love of god, if you have longer hair, or a unique look that isn't that "trendy hip shaved sides thing", watch out. Because it seems like that's all they do. That being said, Todd himself was really nice. He didn't cut my hair, someone else did, but Todd is a cool guy. I probably should have scheduled with him.Honestly, I'm really upset. I'm ashamed. I'm awkward. I lost my look and it got replaced with something I find douchey, overtly "trendy" and unwanted. If this look is up your alley, that's cool. That's what they advertise as, and I should have been more careful. But my soul just got wrecked.




