4646 Mueller BlvdSte 1049Austin, TX 78723


        (512) 476-6633
    






Todd is the man. After moving back to Austin, it took me a while to find the right barber and luckily the best one in town had just set up shop around the corner from my house. 

The place is immaculate - definitely the style that I'd want to have in my own house. And he always has good music on. 

Character-wise, I'm not sure why some people have said he's an a-hole. Is he the most affable person in the world? Probably not. But he's hilarious, and you just have to get him started. One time he and I rescued some baby birds that were separated from their mother and trying to cross a busy street in front of his shop. Would an a-hole do that? 

I've been going every month for the last two years, and I hope that he renews his lease so that I can keep going there for many years to come.







I've been coming to get my haircut here for a little over a year and Todd never fails to make me look my absolute best.  I receive frequent compliments on my hair from strangers and I've referred several friends here as well.  Todd takes great pride in his work and is very meticulous and consistent.  I always walk out of here feeling great and knowing I look good.

The shop is very clean and stylish.  I love the decor and music.  It really feels like a more classical barbershop. Todd keeps a supply of top-notch, hand-picked products in stock.  I've switched over to using what he carries and I've never looked back.  

I'm also thoroughly impressed at Todd's desire to improve his craft.  He goes to trade shows all over the world to learn new techniques and sample the latest products.  It definitely shows in the quality of his haircuts too.  

You will not be disappointed at R Todd Fisher!!







I've been Todd's client for seven years. He's the kind of man you're jealous of because he makes a living off his talent. What he does for a living and what he's really good at are one and the same.

'Remarkably gifted' is another way to put him. I've walked into a bar and had total strangers approach me and ask, "where'd you get your hair done?" For years I've received compliments from friends old and new because of his work. He's not rushed. He's precise, meticulous. The standard haircut service is a 45 to 60 minute affair. He will go over time if it isn't flawless. He will get the fade, blend, or 'disconnect' perfect. The portfolio on his site shows how well he does polished, classic, and modern styles. Not only is that true, but he can just as easily do more 'messy' and 'edgy' looks, which I'm often after. Outside of business hours, he's continuing to refine his craft by traveling and attending various conferences to consume and learn as much as he can. And it's paid off, clearly. He now has his own place, he chooses his own product, he has his own apprentices. You really ought to try him.

I enjoy my visits to his shop. He was clearly taught the art of Southern hospitality. He'll greet you with a hug, offer you a drink. In the chair he's smart, has an attractive sense of humor, he's conversational and charming. But if all you want is to relax quietly, he's just as sensitive to that as well. His store is never noisy. It's never crowded. It's never rushed.

Todd also stocks quality product, including my new favorites Imperial and Layrite. For years I've preferred Kevin Murphy, but I've switched to both of these alternatives at his recommendation, and I love them.

Other yelpers have already mentioned the various positives, and I agree: clean and attractive storefront, excellent taste in music selections, online scheduling is easy (Todd will schedule for you at the store if you can't). Tip: Bring cash to avoid a small card fee when paying.

A final reflection: On most occasions I try my best to 'trick' Todd into giving me a bad haircut. It's never worked. I'll arrive with some wild idea about 'what I want to try next' with my hair. I'm also a terrible communicator. None of this really hinders Todd in the slightest. He listens, talks me through it, makes a couple suggestions of his own, and then works his magic. All these years I've never sat in the chair feeling 'nervous'. Only excited. And all these years I've never gotten out of the chair feeling upset, only happy.







The two stars is for elegant interior design, good music, and complimentary drinks. I'm a pretty particular guy. I'm an eye surgeon in training, a model, and a man with a unique style who knows what he wants. I payed up this time ($50 vs $30) to experience a cut by the owner himself, Todd. I walked in with a mini-man-bun-length hair and showed him multiple pictures of exactly the look I desired (the style sported by Christian Bale in American Psycho and Matt Bomer in White Collar - both pretty consistent, elegant, and classic, relatively long-haired looks, all-around shorter than my initial length). 

The cut I received looks like Rachel Maddow's (short on the sides & back and longer on the top, still significantly shorter than my goal). Now, she's a handsome lady and my cut is not objectively bad- it's just not the one I ordered. Imagine going to a restaurant, ordering a $50 steak and receiving a fish filet instead. Will I survive, and do I still look presentable? Yes. It will, however, take me months to grow my hair out to my desired length. 

The other thing that irked me is the attitude I received. "How old is that picture? Don't you want a hair-do in style?" I replied, "I have my own style." The response- "Then why are you showing me pics of someone else's?" Todd my man, a picture is worth a thousand words. If I was sporting the cut in the pic, I wouldn't be sitting in front of you. The styles I showed you are classic and significantly more aesthetic, in my eyes, than the short-on-the-sides-longer-on-the-top look every hipster from here to SF & W-burg is sporting. 

The bottom line: happiness is the difference between expectations and reality. In medicine we've learned we can no longer get away with practicing paternalistically, we have to take the patient's desires into account and arrive at a shared decision before action is taken. Barbering is even more aesthetically-oriented. Just listen to your customers, look at their pics, and give them what they want (unless they give you free rein) and they will love you for it.







It was such a relief to find Todd about a year and a half ago. He is extremely detailed and consistent with his cuts. I've never been disappointed, and I always look forward to my appointment. 

I seriously doubt there are many barbers in Austin that can match Todd's expertise. His shop is also immaculate and he's fun to talk to.







I've been getting my hair cut by Todd for over five years now, across three different locations. My cut is fairly simple, but has some "challenge" points that Todd is able to navigate with great skill. I always come out of his shop looking my best and feeling like I've had a great experience. 

The new storefront on Mueller Blvd. is one of the nicest barber shops I've ever seen. Great music, complimentary drinks and classic styling enhance the overall experience. I always look forward to my monthly appointments with Todd (for a cut) and Rudy (for a shave and beard trim); these are my "spa days" and a great way to step back from life's daily stresses and just relax for a couple hours. Easy online scheduling is just an added benefit, but be sure to book early as Todd's schedule fills up quickly, especially if you're looking for a weekend appointment.







Reviews here for Todd alternate from 'great barber' to 'total a-hole' and I wouldn't know about the former, but I can attest to the latter.

The shop on Mueller is nice, clean, and full of vinyl records, appointments are relatively hassle free online. These would earn stars except when you're refused service they stop mattering.

I asked for a cut that I could "wash and go without product" to which he responded "Then I am not your barber." No warning of what might happen without product, nor any sales pitch for the value of men's hair products, not even a list of cuts that might work without product (surely there are some!). He simply had me leave.

I took off work, planned for weeks, walked through the rain (there's no parking in front), and was rudely refused service. Of course, in the end, he's correct; he's not my barber.

So if you're looking for a barber, and you want to use (buy) product, I guess you could go here, but don't say I didn't warn you.







Todd has been cutting my hair for 2 years now, he is professional, skilled and affordable.  if you are looking to maintain your style or get  a new one (he has done 3 for me) Todd is your guy.   He has never once been late or canceled on me.  He's good at what he does and a hoot to chat with.







Beautiful yet manly classy shop. My husband loves coming here. He is always greeted in a friendly, respectful manner and the prices are reasonable. When first impressions mattered the most (our wedding, job interviews, etc) he trusted the team here at R Todd Fisher. Sergio was our go to guy but my husband will continue to come here.







Go see Rudy, definitely attention to detail.  Top notch place and was so glad I found this place.  I look forward to going back.  Haven't found a good consistent barber in Vegas so looks like I will be visiting Austin more often.  Make an appointment as they are busy although they did accept me as a walk-in.







Todd is hands down the BEST barber I have ever been too. I was in the military for seven years and had to get weekly haircuts - so I've seen my fair share of barbers. I love that he takes pride in his work, is extremely detail orientated, doesn't rush, and is great to talk too. 

I've tried other barbers in Austin, and the quality of service Todd provides is second to none. Even when he has a busy day, he doesn't try to get me in and out as quick as he can. Previous barbers did this several times which led to a horrible cut. I don't have to worry about this with Todd. The compliments I routinely receive from friends and colleagues demonstrate that Todd consistently provides a great haircut. 

He knows what looks good. Trust him and you won't be disappointed!!







Let me start by saying this is 100% the most soul crushing haircut I've ever received. I'm a guy with a unique look, sometimes it's longer and sometimes it's shorter, but I have a certain look and feel to my hair - I've had it my whole life. It's gone now. Totally devastated. I had longer hair going in, and I asked for the same shape, but within 10 seconds I had an electric razor shearing me like I was in the Army. I'm not the same person. I'm not Adam Levine. I don't like the shaved sides. There was literally no warning. I hate how insanely short it is. So much. And I'm forced to live with it for months and months. There was no discussion, just some light banter and whooosh! instantly my persona is obliterated. It doesn't necessarily look awful - but IT ISNT WHO I AM. I'm not a "fancy hipster". I'm not what they made me into. I had a look and they killed it without second thought. 

I'm a musician who plays a lot of gigs, and let me tell you - I'll be be wearing a beanie for a long time. I played it off cool, because what else am I going to do when (without any warning whatsoever) someone starts shaving my head. Once you drag those f***cking shears across someones scalp, there's no going back. To my barber: don't make irreversible changes to someone who didn't ask for them. My appearance isn't something to be so reckless about. 

Seriously, please, for the love of god, if you have longer hair, or a unique look that isn't that "trendy hip shaved sides thing", watch out. Because it seems like that's all they do. 

That being said, Todd himself was really nice. He didn't cut my hair, someone else did, but Todd is a cool guy. I probably should have scheduled with him.

Honestly, I'm really upset. I'm ashamed. I'm awkward. I lost my look and it got replaced with something I find douchey, overtly "trendy" and unwanted. 

If this look is up your alley, that's cool. That's what they advertise as, and I should have been more careful. But my soul just got wrecked.







Todd has been my barber for the past year.
Haircuts before Todd were obligations. The lack of consistency and attention to detail always bothered me, even in top dollar premier shops.
Frustrated, I decided to see if Todd could help. I expressed what I wanted, and Todd actively listened. He offered valuable feedback, checked my understanding, and proceeded to give me the best haircut I've ever experienced. The attention to detail is unparalleled. 
Every experience afterward has remained top-notch. I now anticipate appointments with Todd.
Todd's personable and very genuine. And on days when I'm feeling less conversational, Todd understands, which I greatly appreciate. 
The complementary trim service between appointments is a great addition, and keeps me looking sharp between cuts.
Administratively, the online scheduling system is convenient and user friendly. If something comes up that needs attention beyond the app, Todd is quick to respond.







Todd is a really fantastic barber with excellent taste, a discerning eye and an innate ability to provide a very clean, sharp and symmetrical cut. I went in for a haircut last year after finding him through Yelp and found my new barber. 

Each of the 7-10 cuts he has provided have been fantastic and very high-quality. He can improve any head of hair and style, but he is probably best know for haircuts for gentlemen, cuts that will make a suit or business casual look really pop, but still look good with bed-head and gym clothes too. 

The shop is super clean and very comfortable, and the music is usually dialed-in to awesome American soul and jazz tracks that are several layers more interesting than the junk-food pop that permeates many places.

If you're considering giving him a try, don't hesitate. He gives the best men's cut in Austin I've found in two decades of living here.







I've been going to Todd for maybe two years now - since before the Mueller shop - and can't imagine going anywhere else. I tried a couple other 'premier' men's barber shops before finding Todd and never found the attention to detail I find here. I especially love that he meticulously ensures the sides/back fade evenly (an issue I've had in the past). While his prior location was closer to where I live / work, the new shop has a great vibe and is much more my style. Todd is very personable which is always great, but he will also let me just sit there and think which I appreciate very much. The ability to schedule online is a great perk as well.







Todd says he's a perfectionist to a fault, but if you're cutting hair the way he does it, you kind of need to be. He takes his time, every time. I've never seen anyone blend the sides of my hair by hand, and so meticulously.

If you are worried about not being able to style your hair every day as good as he does it, let him know and he'll give you a little styling lesson.

Also, how has nobody mentioned the free whiskey? :)







I have been looking for a great men's haircut in Austin since I moved from Chicago. Todd is the guy! He does a wonderful job wth my hair and spends the time needed to get it perfect. Shop is clean and everyone there is friendly. Scheduling system is easy to use. I would recommend Todd to anyone who is looking for a great haircut and good conversation while he is doing it!







This is the best haircut you'll ever get. The reviews are real, the barbers are great, and this shop is my hands down favorite barber in the US.

SirJoe entertained me with witty barber banter while meticulously going through my difficult hair, adding character with each snip.

Go to Floyds if you want a beer and a bad haircut, come to R Todd Fisher's if you want to look like a man.







RTodd Fisher is hands down one of the best barber establishments I have been to. I have been going to Todd for over a year now and I know that there is no other place I'd rather go. The professionalism, attention to detail, most up to date hair styles, and not to mention the immaculate upscale space the shop is located, are just a few of the observations you'll encounter during your visit. Appointments are easily scheduled online and you even get a reminder email the day before your appointment. The hospitality is amazing also. Upon walking through the door, you are greeted by the staff and offered a beverage of choice while you wait. I've never been 100% satisfied with a hair stylist as I am with Todd!!







Todd is an amazing barber and his attention to detail is impeccable. I always leave with a smile on my face and looking and feeling great. Thanks Todd!







