        4/11/2017
    

Reviews here for Todd alternate from 'great barber' to 'total a-hole' and I wouldn't know about the former, but I can attest to the latter.The shop on Mueller is nice, clean, and full of vinyl records, appointments are relatively hassle free online. These would earn stars except when you're refused service they stop mattering.I asked for a cut that I could "wash and go without product" to which he responded "Then I am not your barber." No warning of what might happen without product, nor any sales pitch for the value of men's hair products, not even a list of cuts that might work without product (surely there are some!). He simply had me leave.I took off work, planned for weeks, walked through the rain (there's no parking in front), and was rudely refused service. Of course, in the end, he's correct; he's not my barber.So if you're looking for a barber, and you want to use (buy) product, I guess you could go here, but don't say I didn't warn you.




