        3/8/2017
    

The two stars is for elegant interior design, good music, and complimentary drinks. I'm a pretty particular guy. I'm an eye surgeon in training, a model, and a man with a unique style who knows what he wants. I payed up this time ($50 vs $30) to experience a cut by the owner himself, Todd. I walked in with a mini-man-bun-length hair and showed him multiple pictures of exactly the look I desired (the style sported by Christian Bale in American Psycho and Matt Bomer in White Collar - both pretty consistent, elegant, and classic, relatively long-haired looks, all-around shorter than my initial length). The cut I received looks like Rachel Maddow's (short on the sides & back and longer on the top, still significantly shorter than my goal). Now, she's a handsome lady and my cut is not objectively bad- it's just not the one I ordered. Imagine going to a restaurant, ordering a $50 steak and receiving a fish filet instead. Will I survive, and do I still look presentable? Yes. It will, however, take me months to grow my hair out to my desired length. The other thing that irked me is the attitude I received. "How old is that picture? Don't you want a hair-do in style?" I replied, "I have my own style." The response- "Then why are you showing me pics of someone else's?" Todd my man, a picture is worth a thousand words. If I was sporting the cut in the pic, I wouldn't be sitting in front of you. The styles I showed you are classic and significantly more aesthetic, in my eyes, than the short-on-the-sides-longer-on-the-top look every hipster from here to SF & W-burg is sporting. The bottom line: happiness is the difference between expectations and reality. In medicine we've learned we can no longer get away with practicing paternalistically, we have to take the patient's desires into account and arrive at a shared decision before action is taken. Barbering is even more aesthetically-oriented. Just listen to your customers, look at their pics, and give them what they want (unless they give you free rein) and they will love you for it.




